      "id": "user-input-intro",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## User Input with Scanner\n\nSo far we've been sending output TO the screen. But what about getting input FROM the user?\n\nJava uses the `Scanner` class to read user input.\n\n### Steps:\n1. **Import** the Scanner class: `import java.util.Scanner;`\n2. **Create** a Scanner object: `Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);`\n3. **Read** input using Scanner methods\n4. **Close** the scanner when done: `scanner.close();`\n\n### Scanner Methods:\n\n| Method | What It Reads | Example |\n|--------|--------------|----------|\n| `nextLine()` | A full line of text | `\"Hello World\"` |\n| `next()` | A single word | `\"Hello\"` |\n| `nextInt()` | An integer | `42` |\n| `nextDouble()` | A decimal number | `3.14` |\n| `nextBoolean()` | true or false | `true` |\n\n### Let's try it!",
