      "id": "scanner-gotcha",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Common Gotcha: Mixing `nextLine()` with `nextInt()`/`nextDouble()`\n\nWhen you use `nextInt()` or `nextDouble()`, they DON'T consume the newline character (Enter key). So a `nextLine()` after them will read an empty line!\n\n**Fix**: Add an extra `scanner.nextLine()` after `nextInt()`/`nextDouble()` to consume the leftover newline.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "scanner-gotcha"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "scanner-gotcha-example",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.Scanner;\n\nScanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);\n\n// Reading a number first, then a string\nSystem.out.print(\"Enter your age: \");\nint age = scanner.nextInt();\nscanner.nextLine();  // Consume the leftover newline!\n\nSystem.out.print(\"Enter your city: \");\nString city = scanner.nextLine();  // Now this works correctly\n\nSystem.out.println(\"You are \" + age + \" years old and live in \" + city);\n\nscanner.close();",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
